headline: President and Chief Operating Officer at Ninety Plus Holdings / Ninety Plus Coffee LLC

company.name: Ninety Plus Holdings / Ninety Plus Coffee LLC

values.summary:
Ninety Plus Holdings LLC is a holding company for two operating businesses, Ninety Plus Coffee  (NPC) and Ninety Plus Gesha Estates (NPGE). NPC is a trading and distribution business that purchases green coffee from producers in Ethiopia and Panama and sells the coffee to specialty coffee importers and roasters worldwide. NPGE is a farming and coffee producing business which currently owns a 134 hectare coffee estate in Panama.  We are headquartered in Denver, Colorado, and have offices in Miami, Florida, and Phoenix, Arizona. www.ninetypluscoffee.com 

In 2012, an estimated 19 billion pounds of coffee was exported by coffee producing countries situated in the equatorial latitudes around the world, making it second only to petroleum as the world’s most traded global commodity. Coffee is estimated to be the most consumed drink in the world. Of this total worldwide commodity production, higher quality “specialty coffee”  comprises an estimated 2.5 billion pounds. The highest quality coffee is further classified by the industry as “boutique specialty coffee”  approaching 200 million pounds or approximately 1% of the overall global coffee market. Boutique specialty coffee is the industry's fastest growing sector at an estimated 35% growth in 2011-2012.

Ninety Plus Coffee is recognized as being in the highest echelon of boutique specialty coffee production and distribution companies in the world by its international clientele of importers and roasters. 

NPC is positioned to capitalize on the shift in the coffee business similar to the shift in the wine business of a few decades ago. Educated consumers and early adopters are embracing the merits of distinct varieties of coffee that can be tied directly to region of origin, and quality of processing, roasting and brewing.

Software Engineer at Hack Reactor

values.summary:
Creator of recommendationRaccoon, an easy-to-use collaborative filtering based recommendation engine and NPM module built on top of Node.js and Redis. The engine uses the Jaccard coefficient to determine the similarity between users and k-nearest-neighbors to create recommendations. This module is useful for anyone with a database of users, a database of products/movies/items and the desire to give their users the ability to like/dislike and receive recommendations based on similar users. Raccoon takes care of all the recommendation and rating logic. It can be paired with any database as it does not keep track of any user/item information besides a unique ID.

https://github.com/guymorita/recommendationRaccoon
